I met some inspiring women from Steinhatchee after #Helene. Despite one woman's car being ruined and her carport destroyed, she said, "I'm feeling blessed." 

Her resilience and positivity in the face of hardship are a true testament to the strength of Taylor County residents who just experienced their third hurricane in 13 months.

The destruction in Taylor County is heartbreaking—homes leveled, lives turned upside down. It’s hard to even grasp the scale of the damage. 

I’m deeply thankful for the Taylor County Sheriff's Office, @OHFCSO, @PolkCOSheriff and first responders from across our state who are working together to bring hope to this devastated community.
